prompts/development.md:19:Begin by reading the workspace's default-read surface completely: the workspace-identity marker `MODE.md` (per `specifications/read-contract.md` v4 §1 item 0), the active specifications (per `specifications/engine-manifest.md` §3), the current `SESSION-LOG.md` index, the current `open-issues/index.md`, each close within the §2c 6-session retention window, and — when the file exists — `engine-feedback/INDEX.md` for operator-mediated engine-feedback inbox (per `read-contract.md` v4 §1 item 9). Then enumerate the archive-surface records relevant to this session's subject matter; for each, either read it in full via its archive manifest + chunk references, or declare in the session's honest-limits section why it was not read and what gap that leaves. The default-read and archive surface enumerations are specified canonically in `specifications/read-contract.md`. Build a full picture of what exists before changing anything.
prompts/development.md:23:When the retrieval substrate per `specifications/retrieval-contract.md` v1 is available, the `forward_references(target)` MCP tool returns every line-precise occurrence of an identifier across the indexed corpus (e.g., `forward_references("S054")` enumerates every prior-session record landing-at the current session). It is a useful diagnostic at session open for surfacing scheduled MADs, watchpoint windows, criterion checkpoints, and other forward-commitments that may otherwise be lost in close-narrative-only relay. The tool is additive to the contract minimum (`search` + `resolve_id`) and not required; agents using prose-scan reading still satisfy the read discipline.
prompts/development.md:37:**File-edit claim discipline (added engine-v7 per WX-35-1 forward convention).** At session close, for every file named in the close narrative §1e "development-provenance files amended" (or equivalent), the Case Steward verifies via `git log --oneline <path>` (or equivalent) that the claimed edit was actually committed during the session. If the edit is verified, the claim stands. If the edit was not committed (for whatever reason — omission, revert, out-of-scope), the close narrative must explicitly state "claim retracted; file not edited this session". This convention prevents propagation of claimed-but-unexecuted edits across session boundaries (the Session 035 WX-35-1 pattern: 13 sessions of SESSION-LOG rows claiming OI-004.md edits that were never committed).
prompts/development.md:39:**Cross-family reviewer invocation pattern (added engine-v11 Session 063 per D-228).** At session close, when any Layer 2 trigger condition in `validation-approach.md` v6 §Tier 2.5 fires (engine-definition-touching, substantive-arc-class, Layer 1 (α) WARN/FAIL, (z5) lifecycle event, or operator-discretionary), invoke a non-Claude-family reviewer (codex CLI per S044/S045/S047/S050/S058 precedent; or other acceptable provider per the closed set in `tools/validate.sh` PARTICIPANT_ORGANISATION_CLOSED_SET excluding `anthropic`) to produce `provenance/<NNN-session>/04-tier-2-audit.md` per the audit shape in `validation-approach.md` v6 §Tier 2.5 (frontmatter + §1-§8). Apply the no-recent-perspective-overlap rule (reviewer at session N-close MUST NOT have been a perspective in any MAD whose decisions are being audited at session N-close) prospectively from S064+ onward. When no acceptable reviewer is operationally available, skip with explicit honest-limit recording per `multi-agent-deliberation.md` v4 §Graceful Degradation (record substantive `reason:` + `retry_in_session:`).
prompts/development.md:45:**(z5) Authoritative-not-witness ledger discipline (added engine-v12 per S064 D-233 §10.4-M24).** Per `validation-approach.md` v7 §(z5) authoritative semantics: the ledger is the **source-of-truth** for validation-debt lifecycle state. Close-narrative claims about debt MUST be checkable against ledger. When a close narrates a debt state that diverges from the ledger, either update the ledger to match (if the narrative is correct) OR explain the divergence in §8 with substantive rationale (e.g., "ledger row VD-NNN supersedes per S064 D-233; will close at S066"). Silent divergence is a Tier 2.5 finding per check 28.
prompts/development.md:47:**Explicit Path-justification at every close (added engine-v12 per S064 D-233 §10.4-M24 (z12)).** §7 next-session-recommendation MUST name the recommended Path explicitly (e.g., Path A / Path AS / Path L / Path PD / Path T) AND provide explicit justification (compact form acceptable; one-paragraph minimum). Avoid hiding defaults inside familiar labels. When recommending Path A (Watch), the justification MUST address the 5-condition test per `validation-approach.md` v7 §Tier 2.5 §7 Next-session-shape critique: (1) open issues unprogressed across retention window; (2) inbox untriaged or repeatedly deferred; (3) watchpoints stale; (4) validation debt without affirmative no-action justification; (5) recent closes repeatedly recommend "watch" without operator agenda. If any condition is present, Path A justification MUST address why the active surface can wait + named re-evaluation trigger.
prompts/development.md:49:**Reviewer-prompt-template versioning + lock-in-after-n=2 (added engine-v12 per S064 D-233 §10.4-M21+M22+M24 (z7)).** Reviewer-prompt-templates are workspace-adjacent operational instruments subject to iteration. Templates lock-in after n=2 successful applications; subsequent revision requires explicit deliberation surface (Path PD or Path AS-MAD-execution depending on scope). The (γ) reviewer audit's `reviewer_prompt_template_version` frontmatter field records template version. S063 was v1 (ad-hoc); S064 close uses v2 (revised per S064 D-233 audit shape).
validation-debt/index.md:12:**Authoritative semantics (v7 per S064 D-233 §10.4-M24)**: this ledger is the **source-of-truth** for validation-debt lifecycle state. Frontmatter declares `authoritative: true`. Reviewers audit ledger as authoritative; close-narrative claims about debt MUST be checkable against ledger; ledger-vs-narrative mismatch is a Tier 2.5 finding unless close explains why ledger is stale or superseded with substantive rationale.
validation-debt/index.md:18:Records-family promotion (creating `records/validation-debt/` per `records-contract.md` v1 phase-N) deferred to post-records-substrate phase-2/3 stabilisation per S062 §10.4-M18 reopen warrants. Lightweight-table is the initial implementation per S063 D-228 phase-3 adoption; authoritative-not-witness semantics adopted at S064 per D-233.
