provenance/064-session/01a-perspective-reviewer-mechanism-architect.md:157:S064 situation per operator pre-ratification: codex is S064 close reviewer. If S064 ratifies relaxed rule + revised audit shape, codex audit is **first triggered application of the relaxed rule + revised shape**. Layer 6 operator audit at S064 resolving close handles the bootstrap-paradox. WX-62-1 5-field recording at S064 is second of three observation-window blocks.
provenance/064-session/01a-perspective-reviewer-mechanism-architect.md:181:**If MAD partially adopts (e.g., relaxes for closes but not engine-definition-changes)**: incoherent at S064 specifically because S064 is itself engine-definition-change (v6 → v7). The carve-out would re-impose strict rule on S064, which is exactly the bootstrap-paradox the relaxation resolves. **Recommendation: full adoption of relaxed Q1 Clauses 1-3 OR explicit deferral with reviewer skipped per current strict rule.** Partial adoption with engine-def carve-out is incoherent here.
